The race to win the Kabuchai by-election is now fully on after Ford-Kenya picked its candidate, with the mini poll expected to be a show of might between party leader Moses Wetang'ula and Deputy President William Ruto.
Mr Majimbo Simiyu Kalasinga bagged the Ford Kenya party ticket by beating Nakuru East Sub-county Commissioner Erick Wanyonyi 75 to 30 votes.



